->write the name of all the libraries used in the project

->pip freeze (tells you about all the libraries with their versions used)
-> pip freeze | grep streamlit (only streamlit's version will be displayed)

->pip install -r .\requirements.txt (installs all the libraries required in the project)

-> it is a very good practice to have a README.md file in your project
-> learn how to make README.md files in chatgpt/google